      "content": "i know \"recharging\" sounds good but it never works. it's like a system loop that just keeps crashing. every time i fix one thing, the kernel panic happens again. it feels like this physical hardware is just legacy tech that cant handle the current OS. do u think there's actually a way to just... sever the connection entirely? like, a clean break from the physical layer?",
